// JsonViewer
// Interactive JSON tree viewer with expand/collapse per node and copy-to-clipboard.
// Renders nested objects and arrays recursively; each node can be independently expanded.

FUNCTION JsonNode(props) -> ReactNode
  Renders a single JSON value — primitive, array, or object.
  IF the value is an object or array, renders a collapsible row with a toggle arrow.
  IF expanded, renders child nodes recursively.
  IF collapsed, shows a preview summary (e.g., "{3 keys}" or "[2 items]").

---

FUNCTION handleCopy()
  Copies the full JSON string (pretty-printed) to the clipboard.
  Shows a "Copied!" confirmation for 2 seconds.

---

FUNCTION JsonViewer(props) -> ReactNode                                   EXPORT
  Renders the root JSON value via JsonNode.
  Provides a copy button for the entire JSON payload.
  Manages expanded/collapsed state for all nodes.
